cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper proposes a method for accurate pose estimation of transparent objects using a laser range finder attached to a robot end-effector. This involves sampling points on the glass border and performing iterative closest point registration. This work is relevant to the fields of robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
